NASCAR Whelen All-American Series driver Michael Cherry has been chosen to represent Nationwide Insurance in conjunction with NASCAR's "Drive for Diversity" initiative. The program gives young minority and female drivers the opportunity to compete with established NASCAR teams at the grassroots level. Cherry, 19, from Valrico, Fl., will race for Addis Motorsports at Greenville-Pickens (S.C.) Speedway. The 2009 season will mark Cherry's second year as a member of the Drive for Diversity initiative.

For more about the initiative, visit http://www.nationwide.com/newsroom/030509-NNS-D4D.jsp

For more about the NASCAR Nationwide Series, visit http://www.nationwide.com/series

Sanjaya-ize.com is now live

Sanjaya-ize.com is a Flash widget that ties in with our upcoming TV commercial featuring Sanjaya from American Idol that premieres 8/20/2008.

The widget, which officially goes live on Wednesday afternoon, allows you to try on Sanjaya's own unique style by choosing the hair, clothes and accessories to Sanjaya-ize Yourself.

Depending on which outfit you select, you will hear a different Sanjaya sound clip from the new Nationwide TV commercial as your Sanjaya-ized likeness dances.
